/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Thomas_A._Steitz\" title=\"Thomas A. Steitz\">Thomas A. Steitz<\/a> for her studies on the structure and function of the ribosome, becoming the first Israeli woman to win the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize\" title=\"Nobel Prize\">Nobel Prize<\/a> out of ten Israeli Nobel laureates,<sup id=\"cite_ref-JPost1019_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Ada_E._Yonath#cite_note-JPost1019-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> the first woman from the Middle East to win a Nobel prize in the sciences,<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Ada_E._Yonath#cite_note-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> and the first woman in 45 years to win the Nobel Prize for Chemistry. However, she said herself that there was nothing special about a woman winning the Prize.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Ada_E._Yonath#cite_note-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Ada E. Yonath","place_of_birth":"Jerusalem","place_of_death":null,"text":"Ada E. Yonath , Chemistry, 2009","year":2009.0}